Elizabeth Warren has officially suspended her presidential campaign and now many people are wondering if she will endorse Bernie Sanders in his bid for president.
Such a move won’t necessarily guarantee a vote from the many Black women who backed Warren during her run.
Despite both Warren and Sanders’ progressive stance on issues like universal healthcare, the two still differ in various ways.
— Kimberly Nicole Foster (@KimberlyNFoster) March 5, 2020Many Black women made it clear that with Warren out of the race, a Sanders vote from them is not guaranteed.
https://t.co/6nKhedGRA3 — yvette nicole brown (@YNB) March 5, 2020There were also Black women who vocalized that Biden was not it for them.